Sentencas: Thin film solid electrolytes of La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM), Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC), and Sc0.11Zr0.89O2-delta (ScSZ) were deposited by RF magnetron sputtering onto single crystal sapphire substrates as well as onto porous NiO-SDC anodes at deposition temperatures of RT <= T <= 500 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of thin film electrolytes deposited by RF magnetron sputtering for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivities, phase analyses as deposited and after annealing and microstructures of the deposited thin film electrolytes were examined.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of thin film electrolytes deposited by RF magnetron sputtering for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the electrochemical performance of single cells composed of Sm0.5Sr0.5O3-delta (SSC)+SDC//SDC/ScSZ//NiO+SDC was demonstrated.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of thin film electrolytes deposited by RF magnetron sputtering for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Impervious and highly dense bilayer thin films of SDC and ScSZ have been successfully prepared on porous NiO-SDC anodes.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of thin film electrolytes deposited by RF magnetron sputtering for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Maximum power densities of 360 and 240 MW cm(-2) from single cells of Sm0.5Sr0.5O3-delta (SSC)+SDC//SDC/ScSZ//NiO+SDC were obtained at 600 and 550 degrees C, respectively, under humid 20% H-2 in Ar (3% H2O) and air.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of thin film electrolytes deposited by RF magnetron sputtering for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: RF magnetron sputtering can be applied for depositing high performance thin film electrolytes in low temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of thin film electrolytes deposited by RF magnetron sputtering for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells
